#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/references/implementation.md
M|references|Implementing EOS is not a one-day workshop or a one-month project. It is a systematic, two-year journey that transforms how a company operates. This guide covers the complete implementation timeline, 
M|references|EOS implementation follows a structured sequence of sessions over roughly two years. Each ses builds on the previous one, layering in new tools and reinforcing existing ones.
M|references|| ses | Timing | Duration | Focus |
M|references||---------|--------|----------|-------|
M|references|| **Focus Day** | Month 0 | Full day (8 hours) | Accountability Chart, Rocks, Scorecard, Level 10 Meeting |
M|references|| **Vision Building Day 1** | Month 1 | Full day (8 hours) | Core Values, Core Focus, 10-Year Target, mkt str |
M|references|| **Vision Building Day 2** | Month 2 | Full day (8 hours) | 3-Year Picture, 1-Year Plan, Quarterly Rocks, Issues List |
M|references|| **Quarterly ses 1** | Month 5 | Full day (8 hours) | Rock rv, new rocks, IDS strategic issues |
M|references|| **Quarterly ses 2** | Month 8 | Full day (8 hours) | Rock rv, new rocks, process documentation |
M|references|| **Annual Planning** | Month 11 | 2 days (16 hours) | Full V/TO rv, 1-Year Plan, Q1 rocks for Year 2 |
M|references|| ses | Timing | Duration | Focus |
M|references||---------|--------|----------|-------|
M|references|| **Quarterly ses 3** | Month 14 | Full day (8 hours) | Rock rv, people analysis, process refinement |
M|references|| **Quarterly ses 4** | Month 17 | Full day (8 hours) | Rock rv, scorecard optimization, IDS |
M|references|| **Quarterly ses 5** | Month 20 | Full day (8 hours) | Rock rv, organizational checkup |
M|references|| **Annual Planning 2** | Month 23 | 2 days (16 hours) | Full V/TO rv, assess EOS maturity, plan for independence |
M|references|After Year 2, the company should be self-sufficient in running EOS. The leadership team facilitates their own sessions, and EOS becomes the operating rhythm of the company.
M|references|The Focus Day is the starting point. It installs the foundational tools that create immediate traction.
M|references|| Time | Activity | Details |
M|references||------|----------|---------|
M|references|| 8:00-8:30 | **Welcome and Overview** | What is EOS? The Six Key Components. What to expect today. |
M|references|| 8:30-10:00 | **Accountability Chart** | Structure the organization by function, not people. Define the 3-5 major seats. Identify the Visionary and Integrator. |
M|references|| 10:00-10:15 | Break | |
M|references|| 10:15-11:30 | **Accountability Chart (cont.)** | Assign names to seats. Apply GWC to each person. Identify people issues (do not solve today -- add to Issues List). |
M|references|| 11:30-12:30 | Lunch | |
M|references|| 12:30-2:00 | **Rocks** | Brainstorm and set the first quarter's rocks. Apply SMART criteria. Assign owners. |
M|references|| 2:00-2:15 | Break | |
M|references|| 2:15-3:30 | **Scorecard** | Identify 5-15 weekly metrics. Assign owners. Set goals. Build the first Scorecard. |
M|references|| 3:30-4:30 | **Level 10 Meeting** | Walk through the 90-minute agenda. Practice each section. Schedule the first real Level 10 for next week. |
M|references|| 4:30-5:00 | **Wrap-Up** | rv commitments. Confirm next ses date. Q&A. |
M|references|- [ ] Accountability Chart drafted with names in seats
M|references|- [ ] 3-7 quarterly rocks set with owners
M|references|- [ ] Weekly Scorecard designed with 5-15 metrics
M|references|- [ ] First Level 10 meeting scheduled
M|references|- [ ] People issues identified (not yet solved)
M|references|- [ ] Leadership team aligned on next steps
M|references|VB1 focuses on the Vision side of the V/TO: the long-term identity and direction of the company.
M|references|| Time | Activity | Details |
M|references||------|----------|---------|
M|references|| 8:00-8:30 | **Check-In** | How is EOS going? Wins, struggles, questions since Focus Day. |
M|references|| 8:30-10:30 | **Core Values** | Discovery exercise: gen 50+, consolidate to themes, narrow to 3-7. Define behavioral indicators. |
M|references|| 10:30-10:45 | Break | |
M|references|| 10:45-12:00 | **Core Focus** | Define purpose/cause/passion and niche. Test against current business activities. |
M|references|| 12:00-1:00 | Lunch | |
M|references|| 1:00-2:30 | **10-Year Target** | Set the BHAG. Ensure it is specific, measurable, and inspiring. |
M|references|| 2:30-2:45 | Break | |
M|references|| 2:45-4:30 | **mkt str** | Define target market, three uniques, proven process, guarantee. |
M|references|| 4:30-5:00 | **Wrap-Up** | rv Vision page of V/TO. Confirm completeness. Schedule VB2. |
M|references|- [ ] 3-7 Core Values defined with behavioral indicators
